sentences: Jonathan Kane (born November 4, 1956) is an American musician and composer.
Kane began his professional career while in high school in 1974.
1988 - 2009 - World premier in 1988 of Rhys Chatham's symphony for 100 electric guitars 'An Angel Moves Too Fast To See' features Kane as the only drummer.
1994–present - Forms The Kropotkins with Dave Soldier, Moe Tucker, Lorette Velvette and Charles Burnham.
2005–present - Forms Jonathan Kane's February, tours USA and Europe, releases 5 records/cds on Table of the Elements label and Issue Project Room Editions.
2010–present - Joins X Patsy's with artists Robert Longo, Jon Kessler and actress Barbara Sukowa.
2012–present - Forms Soldier Kane with Dave Soldier
1991 - 2000 - Member of La Monte Young's 'Forever Bad Blues Band' performing Young's 3+ hour piece 'Young's Dorian Blues in G'.
1988 - 2009 - World premier in 1988 of Rhys Chatham's symphony for 100 electric guitars 'An Angel Moves Too Fast To See' features Kane as the only drummer.
1984 - 1988 - Composes and arranges for choreographers Bebe Miller and Lisa Fox
1981 - 1983 - Forms Swans with Michael Gira, forms Transmission with Daniel Galliduani, tours USA with Swans/Sonic Youth 'Savage Blunder Tours', tours with Rhys Chatham on "Kitchen Tour USA 1"
Coming out of New York's Downtown Music scene of the early 1980s, Kane is known for his work with minimalist composers La Monte Young and Rhys Chatham, and was a founding member of NYC band Swans.
1980 - 1981 - NYC post punk band Circus Mort with future Swans front man Michael Gira
He also leads his own minimalist blues band called Jonathan Kane's February.
1977 - 1979 - Attends Berklee College of Music in Boston, MA
2005–present - Forms Jonathan Kane's February, tours USA and Europe, releases 5 records/cds on Table of the Elements label and Issue Project Room Editions.
